r":"Penguin","status":"APPROVED","type":"BOOK","visibleUrl":null,"year":"2014"}],"takeAction":[],"recommendations":[{"__typename":"Recommendation","blurb":"Across radio, print and video the rewilding advocate makes his case for restoring natural food chains. Watch for a sweet Rewilding 101 animation.","recLists":[{"__typename":"RecommendationList","title":"reading list","description":"","recItems":[{"__typename":"RecommendationItem","blurb":"","eyebrow":null,"headline":"Why are Britain\'s conservation groups so lacking in ambition?","isPdf":false,"label":"READ_ARTICLE","linkUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/environment/georgemonbiot/2013/oct/18/uk-carnivores-rewild-wolves-bison-conservation","note":"George Monbiot\\r\\n*The Guardian*, October 18, 2013"},{"__typename":"RecommendationItem","blurb":"","eyebrow":null,"headline":"Rewilding Made Simple","isPdf":false,"label":"WATCH","linkUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/environment/blog/video/2013/may/30/rewilding-animation-george-monbiot-video","note":"George Monbiot et al.\\r\\n*The Guardian*, May 30, 2013 "},{"__typename":"RecommendationItem","blurb":"","eyebrow":null,"headline":"George Monbiot in search of the wild","isPdf":false,"label":"LISTEN","linkUrl":"http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01snjq6","note":"Clare Balding \\r\\nBBC Radio 4, June 6, 2013 "}]}]}]},"primaryImageSet":[{"__typename":"PhotoSize","url":"https://pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/b4a648817c1a2102dc53dc2147bb1af2785067f0_1600x1200.jpg","aspectRatioName":"4x3"}],"relatedVideos":[{"__typename":"Video","slug":"jane_goodall_how_humans_and_animals_can_live_together","id":"340"},{"__typename":"Video","slug":"hendrik_poinar_bring_back_the_woolly_mammoth","id":"1751"},{"__typename":"Video","slug":"stewart_brand_the_dawn_of_de_extinction_are_you_ready","id":"1690"},{"__typename":"Video","slug":"greg_asner_ecology_from_the_air","id":"1874"},{"__typename":"Video","slug":"allan_savory_how_to_fight_desertification_and_reverse_climate_change","id":"1683"},{"__typename":"Video","slug":"asha_de_vos_why_you_should_care_about_whale_poo","id":"2160"}],"customContentDetails":{"__typename":"CustomContentDetails","partnerName":null},"speakers":{"__typename":"AcmeSpeakerConnection","nodes":[{"__typename":"AcmeSpeaker","photoUrl":"https://ted-conferences-speaker-photos-production.s3.amazonaws.com/8c5rmifhblxenv39ytqb3ewr2gpn","firstname":"George","middlename":"","lastname":"Monbiot","description":"Journalist","isLive":true,"title":"","whatOthersSay":"","whoTheyAre":"As an investigative journalist and self-described \\"professional troublemaker,\\" George Monbiot uncovers the complicated truths behind the world\'s most persistent problems.","whyListen":"\\u003cdiv\\u003eAs a young man, George Monbiot spent six years working as an investigative journalist in West Papua, Brazil and East Africa, during which time he was shot at, shipwrecked, beaten up, stung into a poisoned coma by hornets, became lost for days in a rainforest (where he ate rats and insects to avert starvation) and (incorrectly) pronounced clinically dead in a hospital in northern Kenya. Today, he leads a less adventurous life as an author, columnist for the \\u003cem\\u003eGuardian \\u003c/em\\u003eand environmental campaigner. \\u003cbr\\u003e\\u003cbr\\u003e\\u003c/div\\u003e\\u003cdiv\\u003eAmong his books and projects are \\u003ca href=\\"https://geni.us/d1IBSp\\"\\u003e\\u003cem\\u003eFeral: Rewilding the Land, Sea and Human Life\\u003c/em\\u003e\\u003c/a\\u003e; \\u003ca href=\\"https://geni.us/U1q3s\\"\\u003e\\u003cem\\u003eThe Age of Consent\\u003c/em\\u003e\\u003c/a\\u003e; \\u003ca href=\\"https://geni.us/vquSR\\"\\u003e\\u003cem\\u003eHeat: How to Stop the Planet Burning\\u003c/em\\u003e\\u003c/a\\u003e; and \\u003ca href=\\"https://geni.us/Fon2d9x\\"\\u003e\\u003cem\\u003eOut of the Wreckage: A New Politics for an Age of Crisis\\u003c/em\\u003e\\u003c/a\\u003e. His latest book, \\u003ca href=\\"https://geni.us/WswMzfB\\"\\u003e\\u003cem\\u003eRegenesis: Feeding the World Without Devouring the Planet\\u003c/em\\u003e\\u003c/a\\u003e, is a breathtaking vision of a new future for food and for humanity. \\u003cbr\\u003e\\u003cbr\\u003eMonbiot has made a number of viral videos. One of them, \\"\\u003ca href=\\"https://www.filmsforaction.org/watch/how-wolves-change-rivers/\\"\\u003eHow Wolves Change Rivers\\u003c/a\\u003e,\\" based on an extract from his last TED Talk, has been watched 40 million times on YouTube.\\u003c/div\\u003e","slug":"george_monbiot"}]},"description":"Wolves were once native to the US\' Yellowstone National Park -- until hunting wiped them out. But when, in 1995, the wolves began to come back (thanks to an aggressive management program), something interesting happened: the rest of the park began to find a new, more healthful balance. In a bold thought experiment, George Monbiot imagines a wilder world in which humans work to restore the complex, lost natural food chains that once surrounded us.","socialDescription":"Wolves were once native to the US\' Yellowstone National Park -- until hunting wiped them out. But when, in 1995, the wolves began to come back (thanks to an aggressive management program), something interesting happened: the rest of the park began to find a new, more healthful balance. In a bold thought experiment, George Monbiot imagines a wilder world in which humans work to restore the complex, lost natural food chains that once surrounded us.","partnerName":null,"playerData":"{\\"id\\":\\"1816\\",\\"mediaIdentifier\\":\\"consus-pm1735-im9294\\",\\"mediaProjectVersionIdentifier\\":\\"consus-pm1735-im9294\\",\\"duration\\":910,\\"languages\\":[{\\"languageName\\":\\"Greek\\",\\"endonym\\":\\"\\",\\"languageCode\\":\\"el\\",\\"ianaCode\\":\\"el\\",\\"isRtl\\":false},{\\"languageName\\":\\"English\\",\\"endonym\\":\\"English\\",\\"languageCode\\":\\"en\\",\\"ianaCode\\":\\"en\\",\\"isRtl\\":false},{\\"languageName\\":\\"Vietnamese\\",\\"endonym\\":\\"Ting Vit\\",\\"languageCode\\":\\"vi\\",\\"ian